# AI-Powered Trade Search Application — Architecture Design

## 1. Problem Statement

Build a chat-driven trade search application where users enter **natural language queries** (e.g., *"Show me all FX trades above $1M from last week"*) which are translated by an LLM agent into structured queries, executed against a trade server, and results displayed in an AG Grid.

### Key Constraints

| Constraint | Detail |
|------------|--------|
| **Hosting** | Application runs inside an **Electron window** alongside multiple blotters |
| **Authentication** | **TEA token** based auth on Electron window launch |
| **LLM Provider** | **AWS Bedrock** APIs (Copilot access also available) |
| **Data Sensitivity** | Trade data is **sensitive** — LLM must NEVER see actual trade data, only schema/metadata |
| **AG Grid** | Enterprise license available; **SSRM not yet used** but can be adopted |
| **Server API** | Structure TBD — using placeholder format for now |

