## 3. AG Grid Analysis — Is It Suitable?

### Verdict: **Yes, AG Grid is an excellent fit** ✅

AG Grid is already in use and is one of the strongest data grid libraries for this use case. Here's the analysis:

### ✅ Strengths for This Application

| Feature | Benefit |
|---------|---------|
| **AG Grid AI Toolkit** (v34.3+, Enterprise) | Native support for NL → grid state translation via `getStructuredSchema()` and `setState()` APIs |
| **Server-Side Row Model (SSRM)** | Lazy-loads data from server; ideal for large trade datasets (millions of rows) |
| **Dynamic Column Definitions** | Columns can be set/changed at runtime via `setGridOption('columnDefs', newDefs)` — useful when AI returns different result shapes |
| **Built-in Filtering/Sorting** | Column filters, quick filters, and advanced filter support reduce custom work |
| **Excel/CSV Export** | Already used in your codebase; traders expect export functionality |
| **Cell Renderers** | Custom formatting for prices, currencies, status badges, PnL coloring (red/green) |
| **Row Grouping & Aggregation** | Traders can group by counterparty, asset class, etc. with drill-down |
| **Column State Persistence** | Save/restore user column preferences between sessions |

### ⚠️ Considerations

| Concern | Mitigation |
|---------|------------|
| Enterprise license ✅ | Confirmed available |
| **SSRM not currently used** | Can be adopted for this feature — ideal for lazy-loading large trade result sets. Recommend adopting SSRM specifically for this blotter |
| AI Toolkit only controls grid state (filter/sort/group) — it does NOT fetch new data from server | Your architecture must still handle the query→server→data pipeline separately |
| Dynamic columns from AI responses need careful schema mapping | Define a canonical set of trade columns; let AI toggle visibility |

### AG Grid AI Toolkit — How It Works

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant ChatUI
    participant LLM
    participant AGGrid
    participant Server

    User->>ChatUI: "Show FX trades > $1M"
    ChatUI->>AGGrid: gridApi.getStructuredSchema()
    AGGrid-->>ChatUI: Grid schema (filters, sorts, columns)
    ChatUI->>LLM: User query + grid schema + current state
    LLM-->>ChatUI: New grid state JSON
    ChatUI->>AGGrid: gridApi.setState(newState)
    AGGrid->>Server: SSRM data request with new filters/sorts
    Server-->>AGGrid: Trade data rows
    AGGrid-->>User: Rendered results
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Two distinct approaches exist** — the AG Grid AI Toolkit approach (above) manipulates grid filters/sort and then SSRM fetches data, versus a **Custom NL-to-Query** approach where the LLM generates a server query directly. See Section 5 for comparison.

