## 6. LLM Model Recommendations (AWS Bedrock)

Since **AWS Bedrock** is the provisioned provider, model selection is scoped to Bedrock-available models. This is advantageous for data compliance — all inference stays within your AWS region.

### Models Available on Bedrock — Ranked for Structured Query Generation

| Rank | Model | Strengths | Best For | Bedrock Pricing |
|------|-------|-----------|----------|----------------|
| 1 | **Claude 3.5 Sonnet** | Excellent reasoning, best-in-class instruction following, strong structured JSON output, great with financial domain jargon | Primary model for query translation | ~$3 / 1M input, ~$15 / 1M output |
| 2 | **Claude 3 Haiku** | Extremely fast (~200ms), very low cost, good for simpler queries | Fast-path for simple queries; fallback cost savings | ~$0.25 / 1M input, ~$1.25 / 1M output |
| 3 | **Claude 3.5 Haiku** | Balanced speed + accuracy, stronger than Haiku but cheaper than Sonnet | Sweet spot if Sonnet is too expensive at scale | ~$1 / 1M input, ~$5 / 1M output |
| 4 | **Amazon Titan Text** | Native AWS model, lowest latency within Bedrock, no third-party data concerns | If strict no-third-party-model policy exists | AWS-native pricing |
| 5 | **Llama 3.1 70B** (on Bedrock) | Open-weight, strong general performance | If you want to avoid Anthropic/proprietary lock-in | ~$2.70 / 1M tokens |

### 🏆 Recommended Strategy: Tiered Model Routing

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[User Query] --> B{Query Complexity?}
    B -->|Simple<br/>e.g. 'Show FX trades'| C[Claude 3 Haiku<br/>Fast + Cheap]
    B -->|Medium/Complex<br/>e.g. 'Group by counterparty<br/>where notional > 5M'| D[Claude 3.5 Sonnet<br/>High Accuracy]
    C --> E{Valid JSON?}
    D --> E
    E -->|No| F[Retry with<br/>Claude 3.5 Sonnet]
    E -->|Yes| G[Send to Server]
```

> [!TIP]
> **Start with Claude 3.5 Sonnet for all queries** in Phase 1 (simplicity). In Phase 2, add complexity classification and route simple queries to Haiku for cost savings. A simple heuristic: queries under 15 words with no aggregation keywords → Haiku; everything else → Sonnet.

### Why Claude on Bedrock is Ideal Here

- **Data stays in your AWS region** — no data leaves your cloud boundary
- **Bedrock handles auth/scaling** — no API key management; uses IAM roles
- **Structured output support** — Claude excels at JSON Schema constrained output
- **Financial jargon** — Claude is strong with domain-specific terminology (notional, ISIN, counterparty, FX swap, etc.)
- **Already provisioned** — no procurement/compliance overhead

